Oasis - (What's the Story) Morning Glory (flac)

Editorial Reviews -- Jeff Bateman

This big rock candy mountain of an album justifies some if by no means all of the 
poses and pretentious statements made by Manchester's natural-born rock & roll deities. 

A dramatic attempt to rekindle the flames of the original British Invasion, Morning Glory rolls 30 years of Britpop tradition into one irresistible (if achingly self-conscious) whole. 

"Wonderwall" can be read as a Beatles tribute, "Don't Look Back in Anger" feels like a Mott The Hoople anthem and "She's Electric" and "Morning Glory" are chewy pop confections.
